The paper deals with the verification of neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus on robustness and the proposed probabilistic approach suggest that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of abstract interpretation and importance sampling for checking the robustness of neural networks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the mention of real-world inputs and non-adversarial probability distributions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
